        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 1:41PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 141 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Zephyr Cove-Round Hill Village, or near South Lake Tahoe, moving
north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Carson City, South Lake Tahoe, Kings Beach, Incline Village, Dagget
Pass, Spooner Summit, Kingsbury, Incline Village-Crystal Bay,
Glenbrook, Zephyr Cove, Crystal Bay, Genoa, Zephyr Cove-Round Hill
Village, Carnelian Bay, South Lake Tahoe Airport, Lakeview,
Stateline, Heavenly Valley, and Tahoe Vista.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

If on or near Lake Tahoe, get out of the water and move indoors or
inside a vehicle. Remember, lightning can strike out to 10 miles
from the parent thunderstorm. If you can hear thunder, you are close
enough to be struck by lightning. Move to safe shelter now! Do not
be caught on the water in a thunderstorm.</instruction>
